    "body": "For numeric data, there is already the `downcast` keyword in `to_numeric`:\n\n```\nIn [57]: pd.to_numeric(df['x'], downcast='integer')\nOut[57]: \n0    1\n1    2\n2    3\nName: x, dtype: int8\n\nIn [58]: pd.to_numeric(df['x'], downcast='unsigned')\nOut[58]: \n0    1\n1    2\n2    3\nName: x, dtype: uint8\n```\n\nWhile that does give you exactly a `compress_dtypes` function, it can certainly be used to implement such a function rather easily (for numeric values).\n"
